COMMITTEE AMENDMENT

COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 162, L.D. 370
1 SUMMARY
22 This amendment replaces the bill with a resolve. The amendment directs the
33 Department of Education to collect data on the number of mathematics classes required for
44 a high school diploma in the State, estimated costs associated with raising the minimum
55 number of mathematics classes for certain schools and the number of schools that accept
66 credits from alternative mathematics classes toward the requirements for a high school
77 diploma.
